cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SD 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing (NLP) and language modeling. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it proposes probabilistic models based on distributional word similarity. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it deals with estimating the probability of previously unseen word combinations. Finally, it could be classified under cs.SD (Sound) as it mentions speech recognition error reduction.
